Campaign to Ban Land Mines.
NATIONS (AP) _ Burkino Faso became the 40th country to ratify an international treaty to ban anti-personnel land mines  meaning the treaty will go into effect in six months.
International Children's Fund, congratulated the countries that ratified the treaty.
The ban on use, production and stockpiling of the anti-personnel weapon has been signed by 127 countries.
It prohibits the use, production, stockpiling and transferring of anti-personnel land mines.
But the United States has refused to sign the convention, maintaining that land mines are needed on the Korean peninsula to deter North Korea from invading South
